From Nigel Allen Subject FBI Director's Statement on Waco Standoff In the interests of completeness I thought readers of these newsgroups would want to see FBI Director William Sessions' statement as released by the FBI press FBI Director's Statement On Waco Standoff To National Desk Contact Federal Bureau of Investigation Press Office WASHINGTON April The following is a statement by FBI Director William Sessions regarding the Branch Davidian incident in Waco Texas I had hoped to be making a very different statement this After very careful planning and extensive preparation we all thought that today's efforts by the FBI to bring the Branch Davidians out of their compound would result in the peaceful resolution of the stand off or at least meaningful Instead we are faced with devastation and However I have no question that our plan was correct and was conducted with extreme professionalism and I applaud the restraint shown by agents in the face of life threatening gunfire and I thank them for risking their lives to try to end this I have only the greatest admiration for the courage and professionalism of all